cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a method for decentralized stochastic gradient descent, which is a common optimization algorithm used in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with communication delays and graph sparsity, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper uses theoretical analysis and experiments to validate the proposed method, which could place it in cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
